narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Research is fun! Take this course if you're interested in getting into research in ChemE at Yale. Definitely the most interesting experience I've had so far.

Learned about combustion and the work being done to make more "green" fuels. Also learned about engines and the overall efforts to design cleaner fuels and engines. Learned a lot about Yield Sooting Index (YSI) and how our lab measures the sooting tendencies of different compounds. Very cool work that is relevant to modern day issues.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I think that the way that this course is run is great! It gives the students the opportunity to get hands on experience and learn about topics that may not come up in the core classes for their major.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would recommend independent research for any undergraduates who want to go to graduate school or are interested in pursuing research during their careers after Yale.
